ToDo App
This is a simple ToDo Application written in C, which enables users to create, view, and delete to-do items. Built with a user-friendly command-line interface, this application helps users manage their tasks effectively in a sequential list format.

Features
View To-Do List

Displays all tasks with a unique identifier for easy reference.
Add New To-Do

Allows users to add a new task to the list.
Each new task is appended and numbered in sequence.
Delete To-Do

Users can delete a task by entering its corresponding number.
Task numbers are automatically adjusted after deletion to maintain sequential order.
How It Works
Interface

The application welcomes users and presents a menu with options to view, add, or delete tasks, or exit the app.
Adding Tasks

When adding tasks, users are prompted to enter a description. Each task is saved and assigned a unique identifier.
Viewing Tasks

All tasks are displayed in order with their respective identifiers.
Deleting Tasks

Users can delete tasks by specifying their identifier, and the list is automatically renumbered for consistency.
Setup and Usage
Clone the repository.
Compile the code (e.g., using gcc todo.c -o todo).
Run the executable (e.g., ./todo).
Follow the on-screen instructions to manage your tasks.
Future Enhancements
Save tasks to a file to persist between sessions.
Add an option to mark tasks as completed.
Add a search function to find tasks by keywords.
